# Todoclaw — frontend environment variables (Vite)
#
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development and fill in the values printed
# by `supabase start`. .env.local is gitignored; only this .env.example (placeholders)
# is ever committed.
#
# NOTE: every VITE_* var is embedded in the client bundle and is PUBLIC by design.
# The Supabase anon key is safe to ship — Row Level Security is the real access guard.
# The Supabase service-role key bypasses RLS and must NEVER appear here, in any frontend
# file, or in the client bundle. It is server-only and is not used by app code in Stage 1.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Optional (Stage 2): Sentry error reporting. Leave blank to disable Sentry entirely
# (the app no-ops when unset). A DSN is a public ingest URL, not a secret. Create a
# project at sentry.io and paste its DSN here in your .env.local. See docs/SERVICES.md.
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=

# NOTE (ADR-0030): there is deliberately no VITE_OWNER_USER_ID. The owner's identity is server-only
# (the OWNER_USER_ID Edge secret); the frontend asks the `admin` Edge Function's `whoami` action
# whether the caller is the owner, so the owner's user id is never shipped in the client bundle.

# Optional (ADR-0031): Web Push notifications — the VAPID PUBLIC key. Public by design (the private
# key is a server-only Edge secret; generate the pair once with generateVapidKeys() in
# supabase/functions/_shared/web-push.ts). Leave blank and the Settings notifications toggle reports
# "not configured" — no subscription is attempted. See docs/SERVICES.md.
VITE_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
